1
00:00:00,584 --> 00:00:07,500
When we come to the toilets, we go in to relieve ourselves

2
00:00:07,959 --> 00:00:14,626
And showering on Monday or Thursday takes place here

3
00:00:16,751 --> 00:00:19,209
Yes, we used to come in and shower in this place

4
00:00:20,751 --> 00:00:22,125
They bring us a bucket of water

5
00:00:22,626 --> 00:00:26,584
They let us in and give us 15 minutes to shower

6
00:00:27,125 --> 00:00:31,167
Interviewer: Was there soap and cleaning products?
Witness: Yes, there were

7
00:00:31,751 --> 00:00:35,876
Interviewer: Was there hot water in this place, or only cold water?

8
00:00:35,876 --> 00:00:38,417
No, they heated the water for us and mixed it with cold water in the bucket

9
00:00:38,918 --> 00:00:41,250
They gave us one full bucket to shower with, nothing more

10
00:00:41,292 --> 00:00:45,542
Interviewer: Who brought it to the showers?
Witness: He carried it here

11
00:00:46,209 --> 00:00:48,125
Interviewer: You showered with it and gave it back?
Witness: Yes

12
00:00:48,125 --> 00:00:50,584
Interviewer: Was there a specific time limit for showering?

13
00:00:50,584 --> 00:00:53,709
Yes, he told us, Don’t take longer than 15 minutes

14
00:00:53,751 --> 00:00:55,792
Interviewer: And were you allowed to shower anytime you wanted?

15
00:00:55,834 --> 00:00:57,542
No, it was only allowed on Monday and Thursday

16
00:00:58,709 --> 00:01:02,375
Interviewer: During the 28 days you stayed here

17
00:01:02,500 --> 00:01:06,667
Did it ever happen that the toilets or showers got clogged

18
00:01:07,042 --> 00:01:08,334
And did they fix them, or you?

19
00:01:08,375 --> 00:01:09,876
No, we were the ones who cleaned them

20
00:01:10,334 --> 00:01:13,459
Interviewer: Didn’t they ever get clogged?
Witness: No, we cleaned them

21
00:01:13,667 --> 00:01:17,417
Meaning when we finished, we cleaned them, organized them, and then left

22
00:01:17,584 --> 00:01:19,542
Interviewer: Was water available, or did it ever get cut off?

23
00:01:19,584 --> 00:01:20,667
No, they used to bring us water

24
00:01:21,292 --> 00:01:23,584
Interviewer: Didn’t the water ever get cut off?

25
00:01:24,250 --> 00:01:28,125
Sometimes, when there was shelling, the water was cut off

26
00:01:28,792 --> 00:01:30,209
They would bring water with a truck

27
00:01:30,792 --> 00:01:32,375
And transfer the water from it to here

28
00:01:32,876 --> 00:01:37,250
They brought one of the prisoners to carry
the water and bring it to us in this place
